                        <h2>What is UAE Excise Tax?</h2>
                        <p>Introduced in the United Arab Emirates in 2017, the excise tax is a form of indirect tax that is levied on specific excise goods that are deemed to be typically harmful to the health of the general public or the environment, such as excise tax UAE on alcohol and UAE excise tax on sugary drinks. It is applicable to goods that are either imported into the UAE, produced within the UAE or stockpiled in the UAE.</p>
                        <p>The purpose of implementing the UAE excise tax is to reduce the consumption of these harmful specific goods by the general public while also increasing the government's revenue through UAE company tax so it can be spent on beneficial public services.</p>

                        <h2>Which Goods Are Subject to UAE Excise Tax?</h2>
                        <p>The UAE excise tax list specifies the following goods on which the excise tax is applicable:</p>
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>Carbonated Drinks:</strong> Carbonated drinks constitute any aerated beverage except unflavoured aerated water, including any concentrates, gel, or powder extracts that are intended to be made into an aerated beverage. Drinks containing alcohol are not included in the definition of carbonated drinks.</li>
                            <li><strong>Energy Drinks:</strong> Energy drinks are any beverages marketed or sold as energy drinks, and the drinks that may contain stimulant substances that provide mental or physical stimulation, including caffeine, taurine, guarana, and ginseng. Any concentrates, powder, gel or extracts intended to be made into an energy drink are also included in this definition.</li>
                            <li><strong>Tobacco and Tobacco Products:</strong>UAE Excise tax products and tobacco products constitutes any products that fall under Schedule 24 of the GCC Customs Tariff, including cigars, chewing tobacco, and electrically heated cigarettes.</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p>UAE Excise tax products also include electronic smoking devices and tools, liquids used in such devices and tools, and sweetened drinks.</p>
