                        <h2>How to Calculate Excise Tax in UAE?</h2>
                        <ul>
                            <li>
                                The Excise Price shall be the higher of the following two prices:
                                <p>a) The price published by the authority for the excise good in a standard price list.</p>
                                <p>b) The designated retail sales price for the excise good, less the tax included therein.</p>
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                        <ul>
                            <li>
                                To deduct the value of tax included within the designated retail sales price, the calculations to be used are as follows:
                                <p>a) In case of excise goods that are taxable at a rate of 50% of the excise price, the excise tax shall be equivalent to one-third of its designated retail sales price.</p>
                                <p>b) In case of excise goods that are taxable at a rate of 100% of the excise price, the excise tax shall be equivalent to half of its designated retail sales price.</p>
                            </li>
                        </ul>

